sections.title: External links

requirement_evaluations.applicability_reasoning: The requirement R1 pertains to the need for inline citations, but since this section is about external links rather than article content, it is not applicable.
Requirement R5 pertains to supporting statements with reliable sources. However, the External Links section typically contains links to additional resources rather than statements needing citations.
Consistency in citation format (R3) is not relevant for an External Links section, as it does not contain in-text citations.

sections.meta_notes: The 'External links' section appropriately contains links to related resources but does not require citation assessments.
